snippet.textDisplay:
Cavetown:fishbowl
Alec: fishtank
Like the message is basically the same, but different experiences. Like alec's song gives off an aesthetic more like a observatory/ labotoray type. Kindof being an experiment, a human lab rat, just something that has almost no value except being alive.
Cavetown's song is more different, and I cant really describe it well because I haven't heard the song in a while, but It definitely has a different aesthetic and theme. The fishbowl and his astronaut/diver suit symbolize something else. Maybe about not being able to live in your body because of his dysphoria and feeling like he doesnt belong in it. Either way, good work to both of the artists! I'm glad they stood strong ^^

snippet.textDisplay:
... so most of us had a bad year, 2019.
I just hope everyone is going to be happy in 2020 because everything restarts and you'll have 365 new captions and 12 new pages you can decide what you want to do in 2020 . Let your past stay in 2019 and start 2020 with your thoughts for your future,because future is more important than your past, you are not the person that you were 3,4,5,6 years ago forget your past and focus on your future and let your positive thoughts replace your negative thoughts .
Don't start with "new year new me" you would be happier if you do a list where you want to achieve your goals for 2020, and then you can start with your goals for example you want better grades at school,start with working hard and say that you'll give everything and work harder in 2020.
Try to achieve your goals as much as you can and don't give up if you're going to fail, try again and again and you'll be happy at the end,or you give up and be sad forever. I think we all agree with the first one. So never give up things will get tough but be brave and do it achieve your goals!
And you can do another list where you have to write 3 things that you are thankful everyday. Believe me if you do those lists you'll be happier just try it,I'm also trying to do those lists and we'll see the result:)
God bless you all I hope i could help you if you have questions i'll answer you and I hope you are feeling good I wish you all the best xo :)

snippet.textDisplay:
This song reminds me of the person I used to be. It felt like I could never escape the thoughts in my head; like I was trapped with no way to escape. It took me so long to realize my heart was stronger than anything my mind threw at me, and I'm proud to say I've found my freedom. There are tough days, but no longer will my mind hold me prisoner.


Thank you, Alec, for being such an inspiration and wonderful songwriter.

snippet.textDisplay:
I've been listening to your songs for quite a while now, I'd say, and though I still don't feel like it would be really appropriate to call myself a fan, I do like the songs I know.

This one, though... I don't know. This might be a new favourite of mine (well, who am I kidding, it already is, but it might even be an all-time favourite). What struck me as for me personally 'more important' (sorry, I'm not sure how to express what I'm going for, I'm not a native English speaker so I sometimes still struggle with putting in words how I feel about stuff) though was how on one hand I deeply relate with this song/the lyrics to this song and how on the other hand I don't relate to some parts of them at all, even feel contrary. It is an interesting juxtaposition, to me at least, but asides from that, I just really like the song. I think it sounds fantastic, the lyrics are really great, and I overall like your voice (your pronunciation is mostly pretty similar to the English I learn in school so I understand most of what you say which, for me, is usually a big plus for any song. Not a deal-breaker, but a plus).


As stated above, I am not a native speaker. As such, if any of you noticed mistakes I made and/or generally stuff that sounds weird, I'd be grateful if you let me know so I can improve my English.
